Well another boring workweek begins. But I had a pretty good weekend so I can't complain too much. I didn't end up seeing the "Nicas" on Friday because of the flooding caused by that crazy rain storm we had friday. But I ended up chillin with them on Sunday for a while. Saturday night was spent at a nice NY house party. I arrived and found urlLink AlexisT . I stood there in front of her to say hi and she had a 5 second delay untill she finally realized who I was. When asked how long she had been there she responded "too long" HA! but she was a lot of fun as usual. I spent most the night just hanging out and I met urlLink Jerseystyle who has a blog that I read. .flickr-photo { border: solid 2px #000000;}.flickr-yourcomment {}.flickr-frame { text-align: left; padding: 3px;}.flickr-caption { font: 75%;/* color: #666666; */ margin-top: 0px;}.flickr-buddyicon { margin-right:5px; vertical-align:middle; border: solid 1px;}.flickr-postedby { font: 75%;} urlLink urlLink 461568974105_0_ALB , originally uploaded by urlLink mic4te .

I feel pretty good today. Looking forward to a great weekend. Hopefully it will be drama free. It amazes me how some people just love drama in their lives. Anyway, tonight hopefully I will be going to a "Nica" family party. The "Nicas," also known as "the tribe" consists of my best friend and his many, many cousins. I haven't seen some of them in a while so I'm looking forward to it. Not quite sure if I'll be doing anything afterwards. Tomorrow night I will probably be gong to Gramercy for a Birthday party and meet up with Alexis. I love to hang out with urlLink AlexisT , she is so much fun and a great conversation. It should be a great weekend but I try not to get my hopes up. Don't you hate when you get excited for something and its just not that great. We'll have to wait and see. I've been thinking alot the past few days. I've been analyzing myself which I haven't done in a while. I think its because I'm approaching my 24th Birthday and I'm starting to have a little quarter life crisis. I know some of you know what I'm talking about. urlLink Lori from RW Back to New York posted some interesting thoughts about this a year or 2 ago. It's just a weird point in your life where your just trying to figure out what to do with your life. It's kind of scary not knowing what the future holds for you. I'm not even sure what I want to be doing professionally or where I'll be. I spoke to my friend Tina the other day, who is making crazy money doing makeup for weddings on the weekends and she just started a teaching job. It made me think that I really need to start striving for more. I've gotten too comfortable in my little job here and I'm not challenging myself enough. It's all about having the right attitude. I'm trying to replace the negative, insecure thoughts with confident positive ones. Only time will tell. I guess in the meantime I should enjoy all the great things I have going for me and realize how lucky I really am.

What up? This is my first official attempt to have a blog. Don't know how long this will last or how boring it will be. There are 2 main reasons I felt like doing this. 1. I've recently come to the realization that I hold back a lot and I don’t put myself out there enough. I'm too concerned with what people think and that’s just not how I want to be. 2. Need something to do at work. I'm constantly checking other people's blogs so I figure I'll give it a shot. Just want to say that I'm not a writer and can't stand when people feel it's their place to point out clerical and grammatical errors. This is just a blog not a term paper or business letter, so if you are gonna point them out for me ... don't! I will add more links, pics, etc. as I figure this out. Now that that is out of the way, last night I watched another dramatic episode of urlLink Nip Tuck . I can't believe how crazy this show gets. The "next week on Nip Tuck" always looks crazier then the episode you've just seen that topped the previous one. Great show. I'm glad I've got Nip Tuck to look forward to on my Tuesday nights now that Real World is done and urlLink Real World Philadelphia premieres in the fall. I'm such a Real World/ Road Rules fan its disgusting.

None of M. Night's movies can beat The 6th Sense however I thought The Village was just as good as Signs and Unbreakable. Caught the recent episode of urlLink Real Time with Bill Maher . Michael Moore was one of the guests. I'm sorry but he rubs me the wrong way. I haven't seen Fahrenheit 911 yet, not because I donât want to, but simply because I haven't had a chance to. I will probably end up renting it when it comes out and I'm sure it will be released before its election time. I must admit I am a little skeptical about it. I understand how powerful editing can be to make things look a certain way. Look at all those people that have been traumatized by their inaccurate portrayals on reality shows.
